9.    Reports

The following is a description of EPPORA reports.  A key feature of the EPPORA reports is the ability of the user to select which information (columns) for the report is to be displayed along with the order and width of each column.  Section 14 contains the minimal and maximum number of characters for each column.

 

9.1       Budget Report Page

The Budget Report provides Project Managers and Project Portfolio Managers for their projects along with Executives an ability to compare the differences between the selected baseline’s estimated cost and the current estimated cost for one or more projects.  Figure 51 shows how a report is selected and Figure 52 shows an example report.  The Budget Report page is invoked from the Reports Processor page.

Figure 51—Budget Report Page

 

Object Title

Object Type

Accessible By

PM or PPM or Selected Executives

Used to designate the customized report or the default report.

PM or PPM or Executives

Report Content-Width

Number

PM or PPM or Executives

Indicates maximum width for the information.  If an actual column’s information exceeds the width, then depending on the wrap around indicator the additional information is either truncated or printed on the subsequent line in the same column position plus one character position.  A width of zero indicates the information is not printed.

PM or PPM or Executives

Used to designate the title of the report.

Wrap Around - Yes

PM or PPM or Executives

If contents of column are larger than maximum width then “Yes” indicates information will be printed on next line indented one column space.

9.9    Log Report Page

PM or PPM

9.24  Users Report Page

The “Users Report” page provides information about one or more users.  Only the “User’s Name” is required.  Certain information is restricted to a finite set of users, such as hourly salary, productivity factor and cost effectiveness.  These three entities are only available to the user him/herself and Executives.  Each user can obtain their personal report.  Executives can obtain a report about all users, while Project Managers and Project Portfolio Managers can obtain a report about their project team members.  Figure 90 shows an example of the default User Report.  A user can customize a report, as he desires, by selecting/deleting different Information types.  The Users Report is invoked from the Reports menu.
